    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Any substance held at or above its critical temperature and pressure in a fluid state. The properties of a supercritical fluid are intermediate between those of the substance in its gaseous and liquid states. A supercritical fluid can both penetrate material like a gas and dissolve material like a liquid.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
